Title: Euca...Boho Crochet
Body (HTML):
Upon many requests, we are now offering the hand crocheted crop top!!

100% handmade from 100% Acrylic yarn. Triangle shape with long ties that go criss- crossing in the back. Corset style. Crop top length. Beautiful flower pattern in the middle.

Perfect for wearing inside any deep neck outer piece. As you can see we pair it with many of our clothing style. Goes well with just about anything and looks great on its own.

Surely a very practical piece to have in your wardrobe.

Title: Sapin...Yoga Mat Bag
Body (HTML):
The body part is made of strong natural cotton fabric with handmade batik from the Hmong tribal people. Beautiful tribal pattern in blue and white. Rare rare find. The strap is made with the same batik fabric and is fully lined for your comfort. We add a phone pocket at the back of the strap....See picture for details... Can carry on the side or cross-body. The Hmong people are textile genius. For the batik technic, they used hot liquid wax to draw patterns on a fabrics surface before dyeing. In Hmong culture traditionally hemp fabric is usually dyed with natural indigo leaves to make the fabric a dark navy blue color. When applied to the surface of the fabric the wax cools, and drys to act as a resistant against the indigo dye, keeping that part of fabric with the patterns on in the original color. When the dyeing process is complete the wax is removed with heat and the pattern is revealed. Easy to use long brass zipper that are meant to last. Strong and add a raw touch to the bag.
